Problem:
    class HealthSystem {
      private int age;
      private boolean hasHeartDisease;

      public HealthSystem(int age) {
          this.age = age;
          this.hasHeartDisease = false;
      }

      public void updateHealthStatus(boolean smoked, boolean exercises) {
          if (age > 50 && smoked && !exercises) {
              hasHeartDisease = true;
          }
      }

      public boolean diagnose() {
          return hasHeartDisease;
      }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        HealthSystem patient = new HealthSystem(55);
        patient.updateHealthStatus(true, false);
        System.out.println(patient.diagnose());
    }",

If the patient's age was less than 50, would the patient still be diagnosed with heart disease given the current lifestyle choices?
